LORE khenari
FLAGS KHENARI
- Jackal-headed humanoids; civilization from the mortuary-legal culture of
  Akh'enet; psychopomps, balance-keepers, death-administrators
- Death is transaction, not interruption; the death-ledger is a sacred object;
  falsifying records is heresy, not merely crime
- Ritual scarification on outer ears and muzzle encodes lineage, professional
  role, and number of death-ledgers formally closed
- Bellwind Collapse scattered Khenari court families outward; communities now
  found in mortuary districts, as caravan record-keepers, and as traveling
  magistrates for inheritance and road-debt disputes
- The Jackal Synod (Mafdet faction) claims funerary authority using Khenari-
  adjacent theology; actual Khenari view the Synod as usurping their ancestral
  jurisprudence
- Involuntary emotional indicator: the tail communicates what the face does
  not; professional Khenari are trained to control it; they still fail
~
